description:
Seven Avengers out of time, get ripped out from the past, the present and the future, to protect the friend of the Avengers, Rick Jones, from Immortus. In this epic story turn friends to enemies and arch enemies to allies. It develops a battle of cosmic dimensions, which will decide the future of mankind.

Collects: Avengers Forever #1 - 6
name: Vol. 14 - Avengers - Forever, Teil 1

description:
The epic battle of the Avengers through space and time continues! As they travel to Immortus's fortress in the heart of the Limbo Dimension, the heroes discover the terrible truth behind the attacks of their arch enemy. And even though their chances are small, the Avengers have to find a a way, to defeat the Master of Time and save the future of humanity.

Collects: Avengers Forever #7 - 12
name: Vol. 15 - Avengers - Forever, Teil 2

description: With glowing hearts, Archie and friends are heading to Canada! America's neighbor to the north is a big place with a lot of cool places to explore, and the gang is ready to visit everywhere from New Brunswick to Yukon! Check out this collection of Canadian-themed stories and join in on the fun with over 70 pages of content. This special edition can ONLY be found digitally, so download yours today!

PopCap’s immensely popular Plants vs. Zombies game returns to comics with an incredible, zombie-zapping sequel! Young adventurers Patrice Blazing and Nate Timely travel through time to fend off a “fun-dead” invasion spanning several eras in Plants vs. Zombies: Timepocalypse! They’ll have a little help from Crazy Dave, of course—and tons of help from the many new plants they encounter! This hilarious romp is guaranteed to tickle funny bones and thrill your . . . brains. Paul Tobin (Bandette, Prometheus) and Ron Chan (The Guild, Husbands) deliver another hilarious, all-ages, action filled zombie romp to your neighborhood!

The hit video game returns to comics!

A humor-filled adventure that all ages can enjoy!

Tobin and Chan take us on another original Plants vs. Zombies adventure!

A new Plants vs. Zombies comic-book series!

In this issue, Dr. Zomboss creates a sun vacuum, only to have it destroyed by a zombie accidentally dropping Pop Smarts in it. The pieces are thrown across time, and he sends his zombies to find them.

Meanwhile, Crazy Dave has just created a time machine. After finding one of the broken sun vacuum parts, Crazy Dave, his niece Patrice, her friend Nate, and their army of plants go off into the time stream to find the rest of the sun vacuum before the zombies do.

As the newly allied Gus and Creem, two rival gang leaders who’ve formed a tenuous allegiance in order to combat the vampire menace, debate their next move, our tale turns to an old man with a secret…a man once known as the Silver Angel!

Read a new tale, written and illustrated by David Lapham, featuring luchador revenge on the fearsome vampires from the world of Guillermo del Toro and Chuck Hogan’s The Strain!

Read the comic! Watch the series on FX!

The first issue in a monthly series of full-color digital comics by acclaimed comic book colorist and Meathaus member Jim Campbell.

A couple of students from the local art school head to the shore one fine afternoon. Bernard, Dean and Jorge look forward to some serious Frisbee-tossing and are psyched when Astrid shows up to swim, but Gabi is so freaked out she doesn't even want to leave the car. Why is Gabi demanding they head home before dark? Maybe if anyone paid attention to her childhood tales of seaweed harvesting, they'd know something lurks beneath the waves.

A newly expanded version of the At The Shore stories originally serialized in Krachmacher.
40 pages of pirate goodness. Jackson Donfaire, escaped slave turned pirate, navigates uncharted waters and battles the demons that haunt him.

Falling Rock National Park is a comic strip that takes place in a southwestern national park. Park Ranger Dee looks after animal residents Carver, Ernesto, Pam, and Melissa. Funny and sweet, Falling Rock is a pleasant place to visit. Issue #1 features Ernesto acting as a tour guide, the mysterious Uncanny Valley, an intractable truck, and an invisible friend! Reid Psaltis lends an illustrative hand in the "valley" portion of the story The Uncanny Valley.

Falling Rock National Park is a comic strip that takes place in a southwestern national park. Park Ranger Dee looks after animal residents Carver, Ernesto, Pam, and Melissa. Funny and sweet, Falling Rock is a pleasant place to visit. With this issue we begin to see the gag strip format begin to give way to a deeper world-view ala Larry Marders' Tales of The Beanworld or the comics of Jim Woodring.
